<img src="blaney.gif" align=middle hspace=5>

<P><b>Carol A. Blaney</b> is a senior research scientist at
Kimberly-Clark Corp. (1400 Holcomb Bridge Rd., Roswell, GA 30076;
770-587-7226). She has a B.S. degree in chemical engineering from the
University of Houston and a Ph.D. in chemical engineering from the
University of Delaware. Her research interests during the past several
years have focused on using supercritical fluid technology in pulp and
paper industry applications. (Send e-mail to
<a href="mailto:cblaney@kcc.com">cblaney@kcc.com.)</a>

<hr>

<img src="hossain.gif" align=middle hspace=5>

<p><b>Shafi U. Hossain </b>is retired from Kimberly-Clark, where he
was a principal research fellow. His major professional interests were
in the science and technology of pulp and paper with special emphasis
on environmental concerns. He holds an M.Sc. degree in chemistry from
the University of Calcutta (India) and an M.S. degree in chemical
engineering from the University of Minnesota.

