<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>J. Pharm. Sci. - Special Issue</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FCEFD1">
<CENTER>
<H2><I>Journal of Pharmaceutical Sciences</I></H2>

<H3>Special Issue -  December 1996</B></H3>
</CENTER>
<P>
Papers from the Conference on Formulations and Drug Delivery, <br>
Held on October 10-13, 1995, in Boston, Massachusetts
<P>
During October 1995, the American Chemical Society's Division of Biochemical
Technology sponsored a conference that brought together scientists from a
wide variety of academic and industrial locations.  The discussions centered
on the rapid rise of biotechnology that has recently lead to the development
of drugs based on peptides, proteins, polysaccharides, and polynucleotides.
The December 1996 issue of the <I>Journal of Pharmaceutical Sciences</I> contains a
selection of the papers presented at that forum, focusing on the successes
and disappointments of these higher molecular weight drugs in terms of their
formulation and delivery.
<P>
This special issue of the <I>Journal of Pharmaceutical Sciences</I> is your primary
source for accessing these influential papers in this important
pharmaceutical area.  The Table of Contents of the issue is shown below.
<P>
The price of this special issue of the <I>Journal of Pharmaceutical Sciences</I> is
$25 (U.S.  only; outside the U.S., add $4 for surface postage).  To place
your order with a credit card or purchase order, please call 800-227-5558,
ext.  4554 (in the U.S.) or 202-872-4554.  Orders are also accepted by
e-mail, <A HREF="mailto:m_neville@acs.org">m_neville@acs.org</A> 
or fax, 202-872-6303.
<P>

<HR>

<CENTER>
<P><I>Journal of Pharmaceutical Sciences</I><BR>
Volume 85, Number 12 (December, 1996)<BR>
Copyright &copy; 1996 American Chemical Society</P>
</CENTER>
