<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>The Ireland Funds - Applying For A Grant</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../gfx/pattern.gif" link="#0000ff"
vlink="#ff0000">

<IMG WIDTH="295" HEIGHT="69" SRC="apply.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" ALT="Applying For A Grant">
<A NAME="top"></A><A HREF="../welcome.html"><IMG WIDTH="70" HEIGHT="61"
SRC="../gfx/logo4.gif" ALIGN="RIGHT" BORDER="0"></A>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>

<A HREF="../welcome.html"><IMG WIDTH="51" HEIGHT="41"
SRC="../gfx/hibk4.gif"
ALT="Back" BORDER="0" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></A><IMG WIDTH="51" HEIGHT="41"
SRC="../gfx/higryfw4.gif" ALT="Can't go forward" BORDER="0"
ALIGN="MIDDLE"><BR>


<CENTER><IMG WIDTH="532" HEIGHT="8" SRC="../gfx/lnbreak2.gif"
ALT="____________________"></CENTER><BR> 
<B>
<P>
<H3>

If you would like to apply for funding from The Ireland Funds, you should
contact our Dublin office for more information.  When you contact them, they
will be able to answer all questions regarding eligibility and can provide
you with application forms.  All decisions regarding funding are made through
this office with the assistance of The Ireland Funds Advisory Committee, a
cross-community group which represents the many areas that we fund.  The
Dublin office of The Ireland Funds can be reached at 
<A HREF=mailto:ifdublin@iol.ie>ifdublin@iol.ie</A> 
<P>
If you would prefer to write or call, contact them at 
<P>
<UL>
The Ireland Funds<BR>
Oscar Wilde House<BR>
No. 1 Merrion Square<BR>
Dublin 2<BR>
Ireland<BR>
tel. +353-1-662-7878<BR>
fax. +353-1-662-7879

</UL>

</H3>
</B>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH="532" HEIGHT="8" SRC="../gfx/lnbreak2.gif"
ALT="____________________"></CENTER><BR>
 A <B><A HREF="http://www.visunet.ie/visunet/">VISUnet</A></B> created site.
</BODY>
