<H2>The Ceide Fields</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
<HR SIZE="4">
<B>
<H3>
<P>
<IMG WIDTH="321" HEIGHT="223" SRC="ceide.gif" ALIGN="RIGHT" HSPACE="10">
<FONT SIZE=+3>T</FONT>he 5000 year old stone walled fields of Ceide, unearthed by
archaelogists in the early '60s, now hold great cultural and economic promise as
Ceide
Fields, a major tourist attraction and educational center on the North Mayo
coastline.
A grant from The Ireland Funds has provided for the development of the Fields in
myriad ways, from the paving of roads to the construction of a visitors' centre.
<BR CLEAR="RIGHT">
<P>

Find out more information about this historical site in the <A
HREF="http:www.visunet.ie/vip/tourism/mayo/ceide.htm">tourism section</A> of the Virtual Irish
Pub.
</H3>



</B>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH="532" HEIGHT="8" SRC="../gfx/lnbreak2.gif"
ALT="____________________"></CENTER><BR>  A <B><A
HREF="http://www.visunet.ie/visunet/">VISUnet</A></B> created site. 
