Northwest Play Resource Centre Ltd.: Derry, $16,000. To assist this<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">innovative community arts education group that provides facilities<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">for hospitals, the homeless, and youth clubs, to purchase<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">educational aids.<BR>
<P>
<A HREF="#top1">Return to Top of Page</A>

<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="60%">
<P>
<A NAME="o"><FONT SIZE=+3>O</FONT></A>idhreacht Chorca Dhuibhne: Kerry, $53,050. Co operative in the<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">Dingle Peninsula set up to promote community development, to<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">promote employment, and to conserve the heritage and culture of<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">this Irish-speaking area.<BR>

Oiluint Baile: Galway, $8,500. To provide home-visitation programs<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">based on parenting, and club development in the<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">Connemara region.<BR>

Old Museum Arts Centre: Belfast, $29,240. To provide a venue in the<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">heart of the city to present and promote new work by local and<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">visiting artists and to provide access to the arts for inner-city<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">communities.<BR>
<P>
<A HREF="#top1">Return to Top of Page</A>

<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="60%">
<P>
<A NAME="p"><FONT SIZE=+3>P</FONT></A>arents Alone Resource Centre: Dublin, $25,872. To offer advice,<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">information, support, and counseling for one parent families.<BR>

Pop Bar Drop in Centre: Belfast, $28,250. To refurbish an old mill as a<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">drop in center for young people at risk, on a cross community<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">basis.<BR>

Portadown Integrated Primary School: Armagh, $30,840. To develop an<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">integrated primary and nursery school in Portadown.<BR>
<P>
<A HREF="#top1">Return to Top of Page</A>

<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="60%">
<P>

<A NAME="r"><FONT SIZE=+3>R</FONT></A>iverside Map The Bridge Community Centre: Belfast, $12,240. To<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">develop an arts program in a planned multimedia arts center in<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">East Belfast as a stimulus to regeneration.<BR>

Royal Irish Academy Curia Project: Dublin, $305,000. A project funded<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">by Dr. Marianne McDonald of San Diego to develop a computer<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">database relating to early Irish language.<BR>
<P>
<A HREF="#top1">Return to Top of Page</A>

<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="60%">
<P>
<A NAME="s"></A><A HREF="shankill.htm"><FONT SIZE=+3>S</FONT>hankill Community Information Service</A>: Belfast, $23,000. Assists the<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">publication of the "The Shankill People", a newspaper confronting<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">sectarianism and encouraging dialogue and positive development<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">in North and West Belfast.<BR>

Shankill Team Ministry: Belfast, $8,000. A cross community group that<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">provides social services and support to young people at risk.<BR>

Shankill Youth Group: Lurgan, $11,625. To establish a three year pilot<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">cross community project in preventative work with primary school<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">children focusing on physical, social, and spiritual development.<BR>

Sirius Project: Cobh, $70,000. To create a studio for an artist in<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">residence and a permanent training and exhibition space, and to<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">conserve a historic building.<BR>

Spirit of Enniskillen Awards: Belfast, $60,000. To encourage young<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">people 17 to 21 years old from Northern Ireland to work together<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">in cross community groups in projects around the world that<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">address prejudice and conflict.<BR>

Springhill Community House: Belfast, $50,000. Provides<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">educational courses and programs to people in West Belfast.<BR>

Southill House: Limerick, $37,050. Toward the renovation and<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">restoration of the house and the provision of a number of<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">educational programs.<BR>

St. John's Listowel Square: Kerry, $86,140. Toward the reconstruction<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">and refurbishment of St. John's Church as an arts center.<BR>

St. Vincent's Trust: Dublin, $11,750. Working with disadvantaged youth<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">in the areas of training, education, and counseling.<BR>

Strokestown Famine Museum: Roscommon, $16,813. Toward a museum<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">recording the lives of the locals who died or emigrated during the<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">period from 1845 to 1850.<BR>
<P>
<A HREF="#top1">Return to Top of Page</A>

<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="60%">
<P>
<A NAME="t"><FONT SIZE=+3>T</FONT></A>allaght Centre for the Unemployed: Dublin, $17,200. This center<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">assists the unemployed through various advisory and support<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">facilities.<BR>

Team Theatre Company: Dublin, $37,000. A theater in education<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">company working in primary and post primary schools throughout<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">Ireland.<BR>

Togher Preschool and Family Centre: Cork, $16,000. Based in an area<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">where unemployment levels are more than 50 percent, the center<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">provides a range of programs for adults and children.<BR>

<A HREF="kells.htm">Trinity College</A>: Dublin, $ 190,000. To create a new treasury for the<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">Book of Kells and other manuscripts and to develop a major<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">exhibition entitled Treasures of the Mind.<BR>

Triskel Arts Centre: Cork, $16,300. The center offers young people<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">access to and involvement in the cultural life of the city through<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">community arts projects.<BR>

Tyrone Guthrie Centre: Monaghan, $70,248. To assist in the expansion<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">of this internationally renowned artists center, which provides<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">work space and accommodations for artists.<BR>
<P>
<A HREF="#top1">Return to Top of Page</A>

<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="60%">
<P>
<A NAME="u"><FONT SIZE=+3>U</FONT></A>lster Historical Foundation: Belfast, $52,374. To promote an<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">educational program on the Irish migration experience that<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">explores the impact and experiences of Irish migration to<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">Australia and America.<BR>

Una Bhan Tourism co operative Society: Roscommon, $17,200. To<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">preserve the rural population through cultural, economic, and<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">job-creating<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">activities.<BR>

Ulster Peoples College: Belfast, $50,000. To support and train local<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">groups involved in cross community development and educational<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">activities.<BR>
<P>
<A HREF="#top1">Return to Top of Page</A>

<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="60%">
<P>
<A NAME="w"><FONT SIZE=+3>W</FONT></A>exford Arts Centre: Wexford, $12,000. A multimedia arts center<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">with a commitment to community arts.<BR>

Women Together: Belfast, $10,660. A project that supports women in<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">town and country areas who wish to meet in order to develop<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">cross community relationships.<BR>

<A HREF="widic.htm">Women's Information Drop In Centre</A>: Belfast, $36,200. To improve<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">the quality of life on the Lower Ormeau Road, an inner-city<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">interface area in Belfast with a history of sectarian conflict.<BR>
<P>
<A HREF="#top1">Return to Top of Page</A>

<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="60%">
<P>
<A NAME="y"><FONT SIZE=+3>Y</FONT></A>oung Playwrights Programme: Dublin, $16,000. An international<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">organization that provides programs in creative writing, dance,<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">drama, literature, music, and visual arts for people with<BR><IMG WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="1" SRC="../gfx/space.gif">disabilities.<BR>
<P>
<A HREF="#top1">Return to Top of Page</A>

<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="60%">
