<HTML> <HEAD><TITLE>The Ireland Funds - Connections (Page 1)</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../gfx/pattern.gif" link="#0000ff"
vlink="#ff0000">

<A HREF="../connect.htm"><IMG WIDTH="120" HEIGHT="57" SRC="../conn-sml.gif"
ALIGN="RIGHT" BORDER="0"></A>

<A HREF="../connect.htm"><IMG WIDTH="51" HEIGHT="41"
SRC="../../gfx/hibk4.gif" ALT="Back" BORDER="0" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></A> <A
HREF="../connect.htm"><IMG WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="54" SRC="../index.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"
BORDER="0"></A><A
HREF="page2.htm"><IMG WIDTH="51" HEIGHT="41" SRC="../../gfx/hifw4.gif"
ALT="Forward" BORDER="0" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></A><BR>
<BR CLEAR="RIGHT">
<HR SIZE="4">



<B>
<P>
<H2>A special summer camp where "kids can be kids"</H2>
<P>

<IMG WIDTH="258" HEIGHT="187" SRC="graphics/p1a.gif" ALIGN="RIGHT" HSPACE="10">

Working with Paul Newman, founder of the Hole in the Wall Gang Camp in Ashford, Conn.,
the American Ireland Fund has taken a leadership role and joined with Paul Newman in a
special fundraising campaign to support the creation and development of the
Barretstown
Gang Camp, 25 miles from Dublin in County Kildare. To date over $1 million has been
raised of the target $1.7 million. <P> "When I saw Barretstown Castle, I knew
immediately that this was where I wanted the European (Hole in the Wall Gang) camp to
be," actor Paul Newman says. "I imagined a kind of medieval bazaar where children from
different countries could raise a little hell together." <BR CLEAR="RIGHT"> The
Barretstown Gang Camp gives children with serious illnesses, such as cancer and
leukemia, an opportunity to experience the joys of a typical summer camp in an
atmosphere of love, friendship and around-the-clock medical care. The Barretstown Gang
Camp is the first program of its kind in Europe.
<P> 
<A HREF="graphics/p1b.gif"><IMG WIDTH="87" HEIGHT="61" SRC="graphics/p1b-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE"></A> Creative spirits.
<BR CLEAR="LEFT">
<P>
Joining Paul Newman in the campaign to underwrite the Barretstown
Gang Camp are AIF Chairman Tony O'Reilly and his wife Chryss, AIF President Loretta
Brennan Glucksman and AIF Board members Chuck Daly, Richard O'Connor and Mike Roarty.
Also involved are Belfast-born actor and film director Kenneth Branagh, and Richard
Branson, Chairman, Virgin Group of Companies.<BR>
Barretstown staff ensure that each
child meets with success in activities designed to be fun and engaging, to build
confidence and self-esteem, and to help children regain the sense of self-reliance
that
medical treatment so often weakens.

"We cannot thank you all enough
for the wonderful time you gave our son, James, at the Barretstown Gang Camp," said
the
Walsh family. "It was a holiday of a lifetime and he enjoyed every minute of it. You
all do such wonderful work for the children."<BR> Now entering its second year,
Barretstown is modeled on the original Hole in the Wall Gang Camp, which Paul Newman
founded in 1988. The U.S. program enrolls 800 children annually in its special summer
camp and has been both widely acclaimed and oversubscribed, prompting Newman and
others
to launch a second, European-based camp.<BR>
In 1994, 128 children from Ireland, Northern Ireland and the U.S. attended
Barretstown's first camp session, free of
charge. This summer's program will also welcome campers from France, Germany and the
United Kingdom. In addition, Barretstown provides a year-round facility for children
with special needs and the health professionals who serve them.<BR> The Barretstown
Gang Camp is located in the foothills of the Wicklow Mountains on the 500-acre grounds
of Barretstown Castle. Built in the 12th-century, Barretstown Castle is surrounded by
lawns and gardens, a lake, woodlands and rolling fields. The stunning property is
owned
by the Irish Government and in 1994 was leased to the Barretstown Gang Camp for 90
years for a nominal £1 per year. 
<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p1c.gif"><IMG WIDTH="69" HEIGHT="61" SRC="graphics/p1c-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10"
ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE"></A> Barretstown's first campers.
<BR CLEAR="LEFT">
<P>
In June 1994, construction was completed on the first of four planned development
stages. Existing buildings were
converted into arts and crafts workshops, renovated stables and a medical center.
Further improvements are planned including enlargement of the property's lake with
accompanying boathouse; construction of a fully-equipped gymnasium and a 280-seat
theater. <P> "I have discovered anything is possible at this camp. I even got to meet
Mel Gibson. Thank you for giving me the holiday of a lifetime. And next time you see
Paul Newman, thank him, too."<BR> -Gillian,<BR> Barretstown Gang Camper


</B> <P> <CENTER><IMG WIDTH="532" HEIGHT="8" SRC="../../gfx/lnbreak2.gif"
ALT="____________________"></CENTER><BR> A <B><A
HREF="http://www.visunet.ie/visunet/">VISUnet</A></B>
created site. </BODY> </HTML>
</DOC>
