<HR SIZE="4">
<B>
<P>


<H2>The National Gala</H2>

WASHINGTON
<P>

On St. Patrick's Eve, March 16, Vice President Al Gore joined An Taoiseach John
Bruton,
Prime Minister of Ireland, and the Hon. John Hume, M.P for Derry, and many others for
the American Ireland Fund's annual National Gala in Washington, D.C. Hume received the
AIF's National Humanitarian Award.
"I'm obviously honored and grateful for such an evening," he told the Washington Post.
"With so many people of Irish descent here, this focuses their minds on their
homeland,
returns them back to that little island, Ireland."
No one is more responsible for the ongoing peace initiatives in Northern Ireland than
John Hume. In 1979, he became a member of the European Parliament, and in 1984 was
elected the first Catholic to represent Derry in the Parliament at Westminster.
John Bruton, Ireland's Prime Minister, made a special plea for peace. "Our swords must
be put out of commission," said Bruton. "It requires courage and leadership. Until
politicians... begin to talk, we cannot make progress."
Among those attending the AIF National Gala were Sen. Edward Kennedy (D-Mass.); Sen.
Patrick Leahy (D-Vt.); and Sen. Christopher Dodd (D-Conn.) who called the fundraiser,
"a wonderful event that benefits so many."
<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p3a.gif"><IMG WIDTH="48" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p3a-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE"></A> In Washington. Vice President Al Gore.
<BR>
<A HREF="graphics/p3c.gif"><IMG WIDTH="98" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p3c-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A> <BR>John Hume (center) receives the AIF
National Humanitarian Award from Sen. Edward Kennedy and AIF Board Member Paul Quinn.
<BR CLEAR="LEFT">
<P>
<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="50%">
<H2>The Lone Star State was shining</H2>
HOUSTON
<P>
<IMG WIDTH="249" HEIGHT="198" SRC="graphics/p3b.gif" ALIGN="RIGHT">
When the AIF's first ever Houston Gala convened on April 6 at the Houstonian Hotel for
the future of Ireland, a Houston resident and former President George Bush was the
evening's honoree.  Currently at work with Gen. Brent Scowcroft, his former National
Security Advisor, on a book about his Administration's foreign policy achievement,
Bush
resides in Houston with his wife, Barbara. They have five children and 13
grandchildren.
Ralph McElvenny, Jr., Houston Dinner Chairman and President of Texas Holding Company
told the gathering, "We hope to reach out both to persons who may claim some Irish
heritage and to all others who wish to make a difference at an important juncture in
Ireland's history."
<BR CLEAR="RIGHT">
<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="50%">
<P>
<IMG WIDTH="97" HEIGHT="62" SRC="graphics/grant.gif" ALIGN="LEFT"> BUSINESS IN THE
COMMUNITY.<BR>
A private sector group, BITC will employ two Development Officers to work in
disadvantaged parts of Derry.<BR>
AIF grant: $10,000.
<BR CLEAR="LEFT">
</B>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH="532" HEIGHT="8" SRC="../../gfx/lnbreak2.gif"
