<H2>Daniel Ritchie is Heritage Honoree</H2>

DENVER
<P>
Once again, Patrick Broe, Edward Timmins and James Whyte were the evening's
co-chairmen
for the AIF's Rocky Mountain Chapter annual gala on March 2.
Denver supporters honored Chancellor Daniel Ritchie of the University of Denver with
the Rocky Mountain Heritage Award. From 1979 to 1987, Ritchie was President, Chairman
and CEO of Westinghouse Broadcasting Company, Inc. (Group W). He was appointed DU
Chancellor in July 1989.<BR>
Later this year, DU's Office of Internationalization will inaugurate an Irish-American
scholar exchange program through a grant from the American Ireland Fund.
"Dan Ritchie's vision will help expand the Fund's 
mission of Peace, Culture and Charity in Ireland, and between Ireland and Colorado,"
the dinner co-chairmen noted.


<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p9a.gif"><IMG WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p9a-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A> <BR>Denver Dinner Co-Chair Ed Timmins (right)
presents Heritage Award to Chancellor Dan
Ritchie of the University of Denver. William Coors of Coors Brewing looks on.
<BR CLEAR="LEFT">
<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p9b.gif"><IMG WIDTH="129" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p9b-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A> <BR>Rocky Mountain Chapter members include 
(from left), William Coors, Coors Brewing; Kevin McNichols, Dinner Committee; Dan
Ritchie; Father Horrigan; and Pat Broe, Dinner Co-Chair.
<BR CLEAR="LEFT">

<P>
<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="50%">
<P>

<H2>Thanks, Bruce</H2>

HARTFORD
<P>
<IMG WIDTH="272" HEIGHT="173" SRC="graphics/p9c.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">
Officers and directors of the John F. Kennedy Trust joined with AIF supporters to
present former Congressman Bruce Morrison with the "Spirit of Ireland" Award at the
AIF's inaugural event in Hartford on May 6. Morrison is remembered for his efforts to
help secure visas to the U.S. for young Irish people.<BR>
"We applaud Bruce Morrison's success in creating additional life opportunities for
Irish citizens and helping bring about peace to all of Ireland," said Robert Donahue,
president of the Patrons of the John F. Kennedy Trust.<BR>
The JFK Trust was established after the President's visit to Ireland in 1963 by
concerned citizens of Hartford. On hand at the fundraising dinner were Hartford Mayor
Michael Peters; Paddy Quinn, JFK Trust President; and Sheillagh Mulready, JFK Trust
Secretary/Treasurer.
<BR CLEAR="RIGHT">

</B>
