<P>


<H2>Globetrotting with the Confederation of Concern</H2>

<H3>Ireland Fund of France</H3>

French chic combined with Irish elegance to make the recent Ireland Fund of France
gala
at the Royal Hospital, Kilmainham, a glamorous affair, writes the Irish Independent.
Guest of honor was Derry's John Hume who was joined by his wife, Pat Hume, along with
Ireland Fund of France Chairman Pierre Joannon and his wife Annicke Joannon.
Hume received the Ireland Fund of France Award for "his work for peace and
reconciliation in Ireland and his dedication to the ideals of European unity," said
AIF
Chairman Tony O'Reilly. Irish cycling greats Sean Kelly and Stephen Roche also
received
World Cycling Hall of Fame Awards.
<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p10a.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p10a-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A> Jean-Marie Leblanc, director of the Tour de
France (center), presents the World Cycling
Hall of Fame Award to Irish cyclists Sean Kelly (left) and Stephen Roche at the
Ireland
Fund of France gala in Dublin.
<BR CLEAR="LEFT">
<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p10b.gif"><IMG WIDTH="106" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p10b-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A> A team of seven chefs, led by celebrated Cork
restauranteur Michael Clifford (center)
prepared the menu for the fourth annual gala dinner of the Ireland Fund of France on
March 3rd. Michael and his colleagues worked with Georgina O'Sullivan, Director of
Cuisine at the Irish Food Board, shown here with the group.
<BR CLEAR="LEFT">

<P>
<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="50%">
<P>
<H3>Ireland Fund of South Africa</H3>
In Johannesburg at the Sandton Sun Hotel, the Ireland Fund of South Africa was
launched
on June 21 at a fundraising gala 
coinciding with the Rugby World Cup. This Fund will be dedicated to supporting
projects
within South Africa, using Irish people and organizations.





<P>
<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="50%">
<P>
<H3>Ireland Fund of Japan</H3>

<IMG WIDTH="254" HEIGHT="207" SRC="graphics/p10c.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT">
<BR>While in Tokyo on a state visit, President of Ireland Mary Robinson received a
parchment copy of the Ireland Fund of Japan's constitution from Majella Altschuler,
IFJ
President. 
On March 16 the Ireland Fund of Japan hosted the Emerald Ball and later announced
$25,000 to support projects in Ireland.
<BR CLEAR="LEFT">




 


<P>
<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="50%">
<P>
<IMG WIDTH="97" HEIGHT="62" SRC="graphics/grant.gif" ALIGN="LEFT"> SHANKILL WOMEN'S
CENTRE.<BR>
On West Belfast's Shankill Road, this project
 provides support and training for young women 
(14-20) including single mothers.<BR>
AIF grant: $10,000.
<BR CLEAR="LEFT">
