ALT="Forward" BORDER="0" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></A><BR>
<BR CLEAR="RIGHT">
<HR SIZE="4">



<B>
<P>
<CENTER>
<H2> A Message From Kingsley Aikins,<BR>
Chief  Executive of the Ireland Funds</H2>
<P>
</CENTER>
<HR SIZE=2 WIDTH=40%>
<P>
<IMG WIDTH="120" HEIGHT="144" SRC="graphics/p1a.gif" ALIGN="RIGHT" HSPACE="10">

<FONT SIZE=+2>W</FONT>elcome to our new look Connections magazine. I do hope you find the following
pages of interest.
<P>
For the first time on a worldwide base, what we have attempted to do is give you
a feel both for the wide range of activities that the Fund is now involved in
from a fundraising point of view, as well as tell you about projects that we
support in Ireland, North and South.
<P>
In addition, we have included a special report on the Thomas P. "Tip" O'Neill
Chair in Peace Studies at the University of Ulster funded by the American Ireland
Fund. This special project was launched by President Clinton on his recent,
remarkable visit to Ireland.
<P>
By the end of 1995, over 25,000 people had attended 52 Ireland Fund events in 39
cities in 9 countries. The American Ireland Fund and its partner Funds around the
world have now become an extraordinary network of influence linking back to
Ireland, and translating interest and concern into support for hundreds of
projects throughout the length and breadth of the land. In effect, the Ireland
Funds represent a global "community foundation" for Ireland and the Irish people.
<P>
In Ireland, where there are virtually no private foundations, the work of the
Ireland Funds is critical. At the grassroots level, a Funds grant is often the
difference between success or failure for a fledgling organization, and allows
groups to seek additional funding from other sources.
<P>
Ireland in 1996 is an island of great vibrancy, excitement and creativity, eager
to reach out to its extended Irish family and friends overseas. Future
generations may not forgive us if we don't respond as enthusiastically and
generously as possible. I urge you to connect with this movement through the
Ireland Funds and become part of something really dynamic.
<P>
Over 100,000 people will be reading this new Connections. Your feedback, ideas,
criticisms, and suggestions would be most welcome. In the meanwhile, welcome to
the world of the Ireland Funds and every best wish for a great 1996.
<P> 


</B> <P> <CENTER><IMG WIDTH="532" HEIGHT="8" SRC="../../gfx/lnbreak2.gif"
ALT="____________________"></CENTER><BR> A <B><A
HREF="http://www.visunet.ie/visunet/">VISUnet</A></B>
created site. </BODY> </HTML>
