<CENTER>
<H2>WHERE DOES THE MONEY GO?</H2>
</CENTER>

In the last 12 months the Ireland Funds have distributed over $6.6
million to more than 280 programs that work to advance the causes of peace,
culture, education and charity. Through grants ranging from a few thousand
dollars to $50,000, the Fund supports hundreds of projects in nearly every county
of Ireland each year. For many projects, a seed grant from the Fund provides the
leverage necessary to qualify for additional moneys from government agencies and
other organisations.
<P>
Below is a sample of the hundreds of programs throughout Ireland that have
received grant aid from the Ireland Funds in the past year:
<P>
<HR SIZE=3 WIDTH=70%>

