<HEAD><TITLE>The Ireland Funds - Connections (Page 15)</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../gfx/pattern.gif" link="#0000ff"
vlink="#ff0000">

<A HREF="../connect.htm"><IMG WIDTH="120" HEIGHT="57" SRC="../conn-sml.gif"
ALIGN="RIGHT" BORDER="0"></A>

<A HREF="page14.htm"><IMG WIDTH="51" HEIGHT="41"
SRC="../../gfx/hibk4.gif" ALT="Back" BORDER="0" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></A> <A
HREF="index.htm"><IMG WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="54" SRC="../index.gif"
ALIGN="MIDDLE"
BORDER="0"></A><A
HREF="page16.htm"><IMG WIDTH="51" HEIGHT="41"
SRC="../../gfx/hifw4.gif"
ALT="Forward" BORDER="0" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></A><BR>


<BR CLEAR="RIGHT">
<HR SIZE="4"> 
<B>
<CENTER>

<H2>LOS ANGELES</H2>
</CENTER>
<H3>Liam Neeson Wins Heritage Award</H3>
<IMG WIDTH="283" HEIGHT="251" SRC="graphics/p15a.gif" ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10>
<BR>
ON NOVEMBER 2, Irish-born actor Liam Neeson received the 1995 Heritage Award at
Hollywood's annual gala for the American Ireland Fund. He is currently completing
a starring role in Neil Jordan's "Michael Collins."
<P>
The Heritage Award is presented to individuals who, through their services to
humanity, have made extraordinary and lasting contributions toward a fuller
appreciation of Ireland's heritage and culture. Past honorees have
included President Ronald Reagan; Angela Lansbury; Gene Kelly; Maureen O'Hara;
Donald O'Connor; Merv Griffin; Carroll O'Connor; and most recently in 1994,
Dolores Hope.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<P>
Liam Neeson, who studied at Queen's University Belfast, was nominated for an
Academy Award for his portrayal of Oscar Schindler in Steven Speilberg's epic,
"Schindler's List." Earlier in his career, as a member of
Dublin's Abbey Theatre repertory company, Neeson appeared in Brian Friel's
"Translations." In 1993, he made his Broadway debut in a revival of Eugene
O'Neill's "Anna Christie," co-starring Natasha Richardson.
Chaired by Frank Price, the guests who toasted the star were Charles Bronson, Roy
Disney, Bob and Dolores Hope, Colm Meaney, Gregory and Veronique Peck, Sidney
Poitier, and Christian Slater. Musical entertainment was by Phil Coulter and
Peter Yates was master of ceremonies.
<P>
As honoree of the American Ireland Fund's LA gala, Liam Neeson has designated
several organizations in Northern Ireland to receive special grants in his name.
Stadium Youth and Community Centre, located on the Shankill Road in West Belfast,
is a recreational facility that provides a wide range of activities. The Greater
Shankill area is afflicted with high unemployment, crime, and inadequate
educational opportunities. "The Stadium" offers programs to help young people
break the cycle of unemployment.
<P>
Cooperation North, based in Belfast, and Dublin is dedicated to peace and
reconciliation, and enlists the help of people in both communities in Northern
Ireland and on both sides of the border. Its main programs focus
on exchanges, residential conferences and youth camps. Co-operation North also
establishes links between leaders in business, the media and cultural groups.

<P>
<HR SIZE=3 WIDTH=80%>

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p15b.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p15b-sml.gif"
BORDER=0 ALIGN=LEFT></A>
<BR>
Kenneth Branagh with Anne Murphy (left) and Katherine Price at Jimmy's
Restaurant.
