<P>


<H2>Mildred Ryan Bancroft Fund: A Lasting, Loving Legacy</H2>

Ireland Fund endowment by Mildred Ryan Bancroft of Connecticut provided funds to
establish a special "named" fund in her name to support projects that assist in
the education and development of young people in Ireland.
	The Mildred Ryan Bancroft Fund has a particular interest in the counties of
Leitrim and Wexford. Altogether, the Ryan Bancroft Fund aims to provide young
Irish people with better employment opportunities and an improved quality of
life.
	In 1994 and 1995, the American Ireland Fund made a special round of grants
from the Mildred Ryan Bancroft Fund, creating an ongoing and everlasting monument
to her memory and generosity.
<P>
<H3>Carrick-on-Shannon
Rowing Club</H3>
<A HREF="graphics/p8a.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p8a-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A>
Located on the Shannon River between Enniskillen, Co. Tyrone and Athlone, Co.
Westmeath, the Carrick-on-Shannon Rowing Club is the areaÕs only such community
club and a year-round community center for local young people.
	With the assistance of a $20,000 AIF grant in 1995 from the Mildred Ryan
Bancroft Fund, the Club will make extensive and very necessary repairs and
improvements that will increase its ability to serve community members and
attract tourists.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<P>
<H3>CRANN</H3>
<IMG WIDTH="288" HEIGHT="261" SRC="graphics/p8b.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">
Its name means "tree" in Irish, and this volunteer organization with over 1,000
members is dedicated to promoting the planting of broadleaf trees in Ireland.
	A $10,000 AIF grant in 1995 from the Mildred Ryan Bancroft Fund will support
a development and education program Crann began in South Leitrim in 1993,
including 
training workshops for young people; cooperating with local authorities in making
public areas and woodland available to youth groups to plant and manage; and
providing a resource/training manual for youth workers and teachers.
<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>
<P>
<H3>Kellogue Institute</H3>
<A HREF="graphics/p8c.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p8c-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A> 
Established in 1991, the Keelogue Institute operates North/South training and
reconciliation programs in information technology, tourism, organic horticulture,
light engineering, woodwork, construction for disadvantaged young people.
	An AIF grant of $20,000 in 1995 from the Mildred Ryan Bancroft Fund will
allow the Institute to expand the range of its programs and increase the number
of enrolled students to over 100 daily.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p8d.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p8d-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE"></A> Kellogue Institute





</B>
