<H2>A Tale of Two Shankills</H2>

<IMG WIDTH="313" HEIGHT="235" SRC="graphics/p11b.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">

Mention the word Shankill and people think immediately of Belfast. However, less
well 
known is the fact that Dublin also boasts an area known as the Shankill, located
in 
the south of the city. despite name similarities, there has been no interaction
up 
until now between the two areas. Now, Thanks to a grant from the American Ireland

Fund and the drive and energy of William Smith from the Shankill Community
(Belfast) 
and Charles Martin from the Shankill Community (Dublin) the two communities have 
been linked in a unique cross-border project. Groups from both communities have
been 
to visit each other and there are now a series of interchange activities
involving 
schools and other community groups. Highlight of the visit to Dublin was when
both 
groups went to visit President of Ireland, Mary Robinson.

<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p11a.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63"
SRC="graphics/p11a-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A><BR> The children and organizers from
both 
Shankill's pose for a picture and present the President with mementos.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>



</B>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH="532" HEIGHT="8" SRC="../../gfx/lnbreak2.gif"
ALT="____________________"></CENTER><BR>
 A <B><A HREF="http://www.visunet.ie/visunet/">VISUnet</A></B> created site. 
