<P>


<H2>Review of Grants</H2>
<H3>Your Money at Work in 1996</H3>
<P>

<IMG WIDTH="165" HEIGHT="221" SRC="graphics/p19a.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">


<B>An Taisce, Co. Dublin, Ireland</B><BR>
This project has conserved part of Dublin's architectural and social heritage as a 
link with the old craft guild and provides a centre for community activity in the 
inner city. 
<P>
<B>Barretstown Gang Camp, Co. Dublin</B><BR>
The Camp gives children with serious illness, such as cancer and leukemia, an 
opportunity to experience the joys of a typical summer camp in an atmosphere of love, 
friendship and around the clock medical care.
<P>
<B>Belvedere Youth Club, Co. Kildare</B><BR>
For over 60 years the Belvedere Youth Club has offered skills training and social 
facilities to young people in the poorest parts of Dublin.
<P>
<B>Carrick on Shannon Rowing Club, Co. Leitrim, Ireland</B><BR>
The Club is located on the Shannon River and fulfills a great need as a year round 
community center for young people.
<P>
<B>Cashel Diocesan Library, Co. Tipperary</B><BR>
The library has been re-opened to the public with the contributions made from The 
American Ireland Fund. The funding will facilitate restoration and conservation of 
books.
<P>
<B>Corrymeela Community, Belfast, Ireland</B><BR>
This is one of the oldest reconciliation groups in Northern Ireland. This program 
allows people from all parts of the community a chance to meet and work together on a 
variety of issues including religion, politics, family and personal relationships.
<P>
<B>Crann, Co. Leitrim, Ireland</B><BR>
Crann is dedicated to increasing Ireland's broad-leaved tree cover and to providing 
employment in a declining rural area.
<P>
<B>IRD Kiltimagh, Co. Mayo</B><BR>
IRD Kiltimagh promotes enterprise and encourages tourism and industrial development 
in an area where many jobs have been lost. 
<P>
<B>The Keelogue Institute, Co. Leitrim, Ireland</B><BR>
Established in 1991, the Institute operates North/South training and reconciliation 
programs for disadvantaged young people from many areas.
<P>
<B>Muckross Community Center, Co. Kerry</B><BR>
Muckross Community Centre is available to all members of the community and hosts 
social, cultural, civic and economic activities.
<P>
<B>Nexus Ireland, Dublin</B><BR>
Run by the Presbyterian Church they provide a forum for the young to meet and 
communicate freely and to learn the principles of lasting peace.
<P>
<B>Phab Northern Ireland, Belfast</B><BR>
An organization that is committed to the integration of the young, disabled and 
able-bodied people enabling and empowering its members, by providing a range of 
innovative programs that challenge  the barriers which exist against full integration.
<P>
<B>Rural Resettlement Ireland, Clare</B><BR>
This is a high profile program to revitalize rural communities which have become 
de-populated by encouraging unemployed people from the cities and their families to 
occupy abandoned houses and to integrate with the local community. The effect of the 
work has been to help stabilize rural communities which were were in decline.
<P>
<B>Strokestown Park House, Co. Roscommon</B><BR>
The Famine Museum is located on the grounds of the Strokestown Estate, and is the 
finest museum devoted to the rememberance of the Irish Famine. Funding is currently 
facilitating the cataloging of approx. 50,000 items for future display and study.
<P>
<B>University College Cork,  Co. Cork</B><BR>
Having just celebrated their 150th anniversary, UCC is now one of the largest 
universities in Ireland. UCC is one of the primary employers in Cork and enrollment 
is currently increasing at a dramatic rate.
<P>
<B>UCD Graduate School of Business</B><BR>
The UCD Graduate School of Business is one of the largest faculties of Business 
Studies in Europe and offers the widest-ranging business education program in Europe.
<P>
<B>Forge Integrated Primary School, Belfast</B><BR>
Established in 1985, the school provides integrated primary education for children of 
all faiths. Funding enables hundreds of students to receive quality education in an 
environment of openness and tolerance.
<P>
<B>Stadium Youth Center, Belfast</B><BR>
Glenstal Abbey, Limerick Glenstal Abbey provides education to over 200 young men at 
the Abbey high school. The high school enjoys a distinguished reputation around the 
country. Funding is allowing a comprehensive development plan to improve all 
facilities.
<P>
<B>University of Limerick</B><BR>
The University of Limerick is recognized as one of Ireland's most innovative 
educational institutions with a mission of pursuing excellence and relevance in the 
fields of research in partnership with a range of international and national partners.
<P>
<B>Wider Horizons Project</B><BR>
The focus of the project is the professional and personal development of teachers. 
Funding is helping educators effectively deal with the issues unique to youth in 
disadvantaged, urban areas.
<P>
<B>The Herbert Lodge Music School</B><BR>
250 students annually are taught at the Herbert Lodge Music School. In addition to 
art exhibitions the school sponsors classical music concerts for the public twice 
annually.
<P>
<B>Magdalene College</B><BR>
Magdalene College at Cambridge University is home to the Charles Stewart Parnell 
Fellowship. The Fellowship undertakes the study of Irish culture, history, politics 
and language.
<P>
<B>Birr Scientific & Heritage Fund, Co. Offaly</B><BR>
Funding is helping the development and establishment of a science museum at Birr 
Castle. In the last century, Birr was the site of the largest telescope in the world.
<P>
<B>Tyrone Guthrie Centre, Monaghan</B><BR>
A center for internationally renowned artists which provides work space and 
accommodations.
<P>
<B>Royal Irish Academy, Dublin</B><BR>
Funding for the CURIA project is creating a text archive of all Irish material up to 
the Middle Ages as a Thesaurus Liguarum Hibernaie.
<P>
<B>Linen Hall Library, Belfast</B><BR>
Funding is assisting in the construction of strong room facilities in order to 
conserve unique political and historical documents relating to the Northern conflict.
<P>
<B>Kylemore Abbey, Galway</B><BR>
With funding this Benedictine school provides academic excellence and a rewarding and 
maturing experience in a multi-national environment.



<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>



</B>
<P>
