<H2>Heating Up Palm Beach</H2>

<IMG WIDTH="173" HEIGHT="255" SRC="graphics/p22a.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">
Traditionally the American Ireland Fund "season" kicks off with the annual Palm Beach 
Gala Dinner held at the famed Breakers Hotel. 1996 was no exception and perhaps it 
was the ferocity of this year's winter that attracted so many "snowbirds" from New 
York, Boston, Chicago and other points North. (Then again, it might have been the 
promise of a few rounds of golf and the odd cocktail party that was the lure...). 
Indeed we were honored by the attendance of a number of dignitaries from Ireland 
including former President Hillary and his wife and the current Minister for Finance, 
Ruari Quinn. In addition, Presidents of four Irish Universities were in attendance.
<P>
	Mike Gibbons and his hardworking dinner committee put on a terrific evening with 
the highlight being a remarkable speech by the 86 year old Judge Owen McGivern of New 
York and first class entertainment courtesy of Brendan Grace.
<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>	






<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p22b.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p22b-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A> Judge Owen McGivern is presented with his 
award by Loretta Brennan Glucksman and Mike Gibbons.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>

<P>
