<H2>Taking Charge in San Diego</H2>

<IMG WIDTH="306" HEIGHT="197" SRC="graphics/p23d.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">

Over the years, San Diego has carved out a reputation as being a great party. This 
year was the largest ever dinner and very much lived up to its reputation. San Diego 
Chargers Head Coach Bobby Ross was a most popular honoree at the annual AIF Dinner in 
San Diego. He received the AIF Heritage Award which is given annually to a person of 
Irish descent who has made significant contributions to the community.  This year's 
dinner was chaired by Ron Fowler, President & CEO of Mesa Distributing Company and 
John Lynch, Chairman & CEO of Noble Broadcast Group and was attended by the three San 
Diego based national directors of the AIF. Dan Mulvihill, John Lynch and Marianne 
MacDonald.
<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p23a.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p23a-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE"></A> Cheryl and Mike Reidy dancing the night away.

