<H2>Big Hearts in San Fransisco</H2>

<IMG WIDTH="256" HEIGHT="166" SRC="graphics/p24a.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">
The San Francisco chapter of the American Ireland Fund broke all records for 
attendance and money raised when they held their annual dinner on March 9th. The 
reason for this was the choice of honoree, Tom Tracy who attracted a terrific wave of 
support. In addition the Dinner Chairman Philip Stapleton introduced many newcomers 
to the Fund. Besides honoring Tom Tracy and his family a special award and tribute 
was paid to the retiring West Coast Director of the AIF, Tom Jordan. First class 
entertainment was provided by Hal Roach and Phil Coulter.
<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>

<P>
