<H2>The Big Show: Washington D.C.</H2>

<IMG WIDTH="234" HEIGHT="241" SRC="graphics/p25d.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT">

The last three years have seen dramatic growth in the size and importance of the 
Washington National Gala under the guidance of dinner chairman Paul Quinn. This year 
the event, attended by 1,000 people, was held in the stunning National Building 
Museum, probably the most magnificent venue ever used by the AIF. The list of 
attendees was impressive, headed by First Lady, Hillary Rodham Clinton. Other 
speakers included the Chairman of the Democratic Party, Chris Dodd, head of Friends 
of Ireland, Jim Walsh, Congressman Ben Gilman, President of the AFL/CIO John Sweeney 
and National President of The American Ireland Fund, Loretta Brennan Glucksman. The 
Prime Minister of Ireland, John Bruton, gave a stirring speech and the audience 
included leaders of all the major parties in Northern Ireland as well as British and 
Irish cabinet ministers and over 100 U.S. Congressmen and Senators as well as 
representatives of major U.S. companies with operations in Ireland. The dinner which 
was co-chaired by Ginny Grenham and Paul Quinn was a major success and the evening 
was topped off  by everybody congregating in a unique Irish Pub, specially built for 
the evening which had been sponsored and amply stocked by Murphy's Irish Stout.

<BR CLEAR=LEFT>

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p25a.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p25a-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE"></A> The venue: Washington's
magnificent Pension Building.

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p25b.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p25b-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE"></A> First Lady Hillary Rodham Clinton.

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p25c.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p25c-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE"></A> AIF Board Director Pat Rooney with 
Senator Connie Mack.

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p25e.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p25e-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A><BR> Boston's Bill Connell (left) and Father 
Monan of Boston College (right).
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p25f.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p25f-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE"></A> Ted Smyth of Heinz with Irish Prime 
Minister John Bruton.

