<H2>Partying in Pittsburgh</H2>

<IMG WIDTH="178" HEIGHT="258" SRC="graphics/p28a.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">
For the third time in 12 months the American Ireland Fund raised over $1 million 
dollars AT A single event and this time it was Pittsburgh thanks to the generosity of 
Tony and Chryss O'Reilly, Lew and Loretta Glucksman and Joe Bogdanovich.  The dinner 
honored the latter, a legend in the U.S. fishing industry as President of Starkist 
Tuna.  Just weeks before the dinner he had visited a number of Ireland Fund projects 
which included a tour of Dublin Harbor aboard the Dun Laoighaire Lifeboat - Dublin's 
sea rescue service which is both a volunteer organization and funded by private 
donations. The dinner also honored Kevin McClatchey who has recently become the owner 
of Pittsburgh's baseball team The Pirates. One of the highlights of the record 
breaking evening from every point of view was an extraordinary one hour virtuoso 
performance from Bill Cosby who had donated his services to the American Ireland Fund 
for the evening.
<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p28b.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p28b-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE"></A> Honoree Joe Bogdanovich with AIF Chairman Tony O'Reilly.

