<H2>Big Apple Bash</H2>

<IMG WIDTH="178" HEIGHT="225" SRC="graphics/p30a.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">

The American Ireland Funds' 21st dinner in the Big Apple was certainly a night to 
remember with a whole series of highlights. Nearly 1,200 people were welcomed by AIF 
Chairman, Tony O'Reilly to a huge marquee attached to the Tavern on the Green and 
paid tribute to the night's honorees Mike Roarty and Liam Neeson. The latter received 
the AIF's Performaing Arts Award for 1996 which was presented to him by last year's 
winner Neil Jordan. The evergreen Mike Roarty had the audience in stitches with his 
stories and accolades were also given to Allied Irish Bank's Jerry Casey who 
co-chaired the dinner with Tony O'Reilly. A dramatic highlight of the evening was the 
surprise announcement of a $1 million gift to The Amercian Ireland Fund by Lew 
Glucksman who received a standing ovation for his generosity.


