<H2>New Zealand</H2>

<P>
<IMG WIDTH="234" HEIGHT="204" SRC="graphics/p31.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">

The chairman of the Ireland Fund of New Zealand, Sir Michael Fay is one of the best 
known Business and sporting personalities of New Zealand. He received his Knighthood 
in 1990 for services to merchant banking and yachting, in recognition of the role he 
played in leading New Zealand's challenges for the America's Cup in Australia in 
1986/87 and San Diego in 1988 and 1982. New Zealand subsequently won the America's 
Cup in San Diego in 1995. He is joint Chief Executive of Fay Richwhite and Company Ltd.

A New Zealand based investment bank which has principal investments in the U.K., 
Australia, New Zealand and Fiji. A graduate in law from Victoria University in 
Wellington, he is also honorary Consul General for Thailand. Sir Michael knows 
Ireland well as he recently took a year long sabbatical there which allowed him, 
among many other things, to fine tune his short game on some of Ireland's best links 
courses.

<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
For more information about
The Ireland Fund of New Zealand, contact Oliver Lee,<BR>
The Ireland Fund of New Zealand,
2 Stroke 13, Horoata Road,
Takapuna, Auckland, New Zealand<BR>
Tel: (09) 436-6966:<BR>
Fax: (09) 486-6955



</B>
