<H2>Success Down Under in Australia</H2>

<IMG WIDTH="151" HEIGHT="226" SRC="graphics/p33a.gif" HSPACE="10" VSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">

John O'Neill: One of Sydney's best known businessmen, John O'Neill, is chairman of 
The Australian Ireland Fund. Trained as a lawyer, John was Chief Executive Officer of 
the State Bank of New South Wales for 8 years until June of 1995. He then took over 
as Managing Director and CEO of the Australian Rugby Union Ltd. Australia was World 
Rugby Champion from 1991 to 1995. John takes over control of Australian Rugby at a 
time of rapid change in the structure of the game. John's Irish roots are on both 
sides. His grandfather is an O'Neill from Kerry and his grandmother a Galvin from 
Clare. John is particularly looking forward to next November when Australia will play 
Ireland in Dublin.
<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>

Towards the end of 1995 the Australian Ireland Fund held a remarkably successful 
garden party which realized a profit of over $140,000 which allowed them to support 
the following projects in Ireland: The Belfast Community Circus School  *  The 
Committee for the Administration of Justice * Londonderry YMCA * The Phoenix Trust * 
Shankhill Community Information Service * West Belfast Festival * Women's Information 
Drop-in Centre * Women Together. The Fund has also decided to co-fund the residency 
for Australian writers at the Tyrone Guthrie Centre for Artists in Co. Monaghan, 
Ireland. The proposal is for an Australian writer to visit the Centre for three 
months. The Fund also received $5,000 for the Irish Wheelchair Association from the 
Lansdowne Club's annual St. Patrick's Day lunch in Sydney. Fund directors Peter and 
Jane Cosgrove, Margaret Whitlam, Charles Curran and Patrick Lynam attended the lunch 
and the guest of honor was Irish government minister Avril Doyle.






<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p33b.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p33b-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A><BR> Peter Brennan of the Lansdowne Club, Bruce Peters of Aer Lingus, prize winner Kevin Doherty, 
Alastair Lindsay of Singapore Airlines and Ambassador Richard O'Brien of The 
Australian Ireland Fund.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p33c.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p33c-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A><BR> Lansdowne Club Chairman Peter Brennan 
presents a check to The Australian Ireland Fund's Peter Cosgrove.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
For more information about The Australian Ireland Fund, contact<BR>
Teresa Keating, Executive Secretary, The Australian Ireland Fund, 36 Carrington 
Street, Level 5, Sydney, New South Wales, Australia<BR>
Tel: (02) 262-2892: Fax: (02) 262-2913


