<H2>13th Annual St. Patrick's Day Luncheon Canada</H2>

<IMG WIDTH="211" HEIGHT="219" SRC="graphics/p34a.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">

Wit, warmth and wisdom was the theme of this year's annual luncheon. over 1,100 
people arrived to share in an afternoon of the best Irish fun, entertainment and food.
 Certainly the warmth and wit were very much in evidence at the pre lunch reception 
where Kilkenny Cream Ale in cans was being launched in Canada by Guinness. 
Entertainment was provided by Inishowen, a group of traditional Irish musicians.
<P> 
	Fourteen fortunate people who each generously donated $5,000 to The Ireland Fund 
of Canada for the honour of being an honorary Irish person for the day, were each 
presented with a scroll listing the privileges this position bestows. Included in 
these special gifts are "Exemption from Murphy's Law", "The Gift of Blarney", and 
"Entry into Tir na nOg". One hundred people have been inducted into this prestigious 
group over the years.
<P>
	Hal Roach kept everyone laughing for forty five minutes and surpassed his 
reputation as "Ireland's funniest man". At the post luncheon party people danced to 
the music of the Frankie Benson Band and enjoyed Irish Coffees. Mr. Tom Savage, 
Chairman of the National Board of The Ireland Fund of Canada welcomed Mr. Brendan 
Howlin, Minister of the Environment who brought greetings from the Taoiseach. Mr. 
Ronan Corvin first Secretary, Irish Embassy, Ottowa also attended. The British High 
Commissioner, Mr. Anthony Goodenough and the British Consul General were also in 
attendance. Mr. John Clare was chairman of the luncheon. His committee from the 
Toronto Chapter of the Ireland Fund and the volunteers who worked tirelessly to 
ensure the incredible success of the event are to be congratulated.
	

<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>


<P>
