<H2>Great Sports in Great Britain</H2>

<IMG WIDTH="169" HEIGHT="242" SRC="graphics/p35a.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">

<H3>Ireland Fund of Great Britian Greyhound Racing Evening</H3>
The 1996 fundraising year kicked off once again on March 4th with Mr. Patsy Bryne, a 
wonderful supporter of The Ireland Fund of Great Britain, spearheading the widely 
enjoyed Greyhound Racing Evening at the famous Wembley Stadium. Always a fabulous 
evening full of humor, and one could literally say "all the fun of the fair".
 
<H3>Ireland Fund of Great Britian Ascot Racing Dinner</H3>
Everyone loves horses and everyone loves Ascot so it will come as no surprise to 
anyone that tickets for the Ascot Racing Dinner were the "hottest tickets in town". 
David Reid Scott and Stephen Quinn together with the jockeys, trainers, tipsters and 
personalities from the world of show business, ensured that no stone would be left 
unturned in order to give everyone an enjoyable evening, the only thing they could 
not guarantee were the winners!


