<BR CLEAR="RIGHT">
<HR SIZE="4"> 
<B>
<CENTER>
<H2>CANADA</H2>
</CENTER>
<H3>Ireland Fund of Canada</H3>
<IMG WIDTH="221" HEIGHT="177" SRC="graphics/p19a.gif" ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10>
<BR>
With "Peace and Reconciliation" as its theme, the Ireland Fund of Canada held its
annual fall gala in Toronto on November 3 at the city's convention center. Dinner
chairman was Thomas Savage, chairman and president of North American Trust, who
is also the new national IFC chairman.
Entertainment included musical performances by the Carlton Show Band and Ciaran
Sheehan, Irish-born star of Toronto's "Phantom."
<P>
In October, the IFC held its first "CEO Breakfast". Corporate donors from
throughout Toronto's business community heard Diane Francis, Financial Post
editor.
"At the Ireland Fund of Canada, we have raised our goals and our expectations
about our fundraising events," says Bill Neill, Belfast-born vice president of
the Financial Post and a member of the IFC's national board. "The ceasefire in
Northern Ireland has added extra vigor to our efforts. If, through our grants, we
can encourage entrepreneurship and
programs such as integrated education, we can make a lasting contribution to the
peace process."
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<P>
Earlier this year, the Lord Mayors of Dublin and Belfast were guests for an
Ireland Fund of Canada fundraiser hosted with Co-operation North and Toronto's
Mayor Barbara Hall. The special evening preceded a series of St. Patrick's Day
events on behalf of the IFC held across Canada.
<P>
In Toronto on March 17, the Fund's twelfth annual St. Patrick's Luncheon at the
Metro Toronto Convention Centre attracted more than 1,100 leading business
people, politicians and professionals including Catherine Graham, former IFC
chair and Peggy Delaney, one of the luncheon's founding members. Businessman Jim
Keating said, "This is a day when everyone can get together and toast Ireland."
<P>
Elsewhere, the St. Patrick's Society of Montreal joined the IFC for a March 17
benefit dinner. At the Westin Hotel, Edmonton area supporters attended a St.
Patrick's Emerald Ball hosted by Doodie Cahill, Edmonton Chapter Chairman, and
Colm O'Carroll, Vice Chairman.
<P>
On May 5, the IFC's Ottawa Chapter held its fifth annual Emerald Ball at the
Chateau Laurier Hotel with entertainment by the local branch of Comhaltas
Ceoltoiri Eireann. Dinner chairmen for the festive evening were Pat Whelan and
Chris Murray.
<P>
<HR SIZE=3 WIDTH=80%>

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p19b.gif"><IMG WIDTH="53" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p19b-sml.gif"
BORDER=0 ALIGN=LEFT></A>
<BR>
At the 1995 Toronto Gala Ireland Fund of Canada Chairman Tom Savage presents past
Chairperson Catherine Graham with a Waterford bowl.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p19c.gif"><IMG WIDTH="52" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p19c-sml.gif"
