<BR CLEAR="RIGHT">
<HR SIZE="4">
<B>
<P>


<H2>Mildred Ryan Bancroft Fund: A Lasting, Loving Legacy</H2>

<H3>Mohill Heritage Railway Restoration Society</H3>
<A HREF="graphics/p9c.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p9c-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A>
Formed in 1993, the Society aims to restore railway linkage between Mohill and
Dromod, Co. Leitrim, as part of a tourism development effort to encourage
investment and jobs creation. The project complements the Ballyconnell canal
project, which recently linked the River Shannon and Lough Erne, two of Ireland's
major waterways.
	In 1994, an AIF grant of over $22,000 from the Mildred Ryan Bancroft Fund
will enable the Society to develop the historic Mohill Station House as a local
heritage center and museum, in addition to its railway use.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<P>
<H3>Old Barrel Store &
Crafts Co-Op</H3>

<A HREF="graphics/p9b.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p9b-sml.gif"
BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="LEFT"></A>
Now a recognized center displaying high quality crafts, the Co-op in
Carrick-on-Shannon, Co. Leitrim was formed in 1987 by local artists concerned
that there was no outlet for the promotion and sale of their work.
	An AIF grant in 1995 of over $15,000 from the Mildred Ryan Bancroft Fund will
allow the Co-op to continue to link art and business development through
workshops in various arts and crafts open to residents and visitors.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<P>
<H3>Westford Opera Festival</H3>
<IMG WIDTH="238" HEIGHT="208" SRC="graphics/p9a.gif" HSPACE="10" ALIGN="RIGHT">
One of the most prestigious and celebrated Irish cultural festivals, the Wexford
Opera Festival attracts a host of performing artists as well as local and
international audiences. The Festival has also spurred considerable local
development and injected millions into the Wexford area economy.
	An AIF grant of over $22,000 from the Mildred Ryan Bancroft Fund in 1994 will
develop a "mini-festival" for Wexford children that is designed to stimulate
interest in the arts and create a sense of local ownership in the Festival.
<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>

</B>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH="532" HEIGHT="8" SRC="../../gfx/lnbreak2.gif"
