<H2>AIF Literary Award Winners</H2>

<H3>1979 Award Recipient was 83</H3>
Mary Lavin, who was born in Massachusetts and moved to 
Athenry, Co. Galway when she was nine years old, died in Dublin on March 25.
<P>
	In her novels and short stories, Lavin depicted the subtleties of Irish small-town 
life with a grace that won her the 1979 AIF Literary Award as well as several 
Gugenheim Fellowships and the Katherine Mansfield Prize. She published 19 short story 
collections and two novels.
<P>
	Other AIF Literary Award winners who have died are Austin Clarke, Hubert Butler, 
Michael McLaverty, and Sean O Faolain.
<P>
