<CENTER>

<H2>GERMANY</H2>
</CENTER>
<H3>German Ireland Fund</H3>
<IMG WIDTH="180" HEIGHT="210" SRC="graphics/p25a.gif" ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10>
<BR>
KOLN - The German Ireland Fund was founded in 1992, according to Ines Koerdt, the
Fund's Executive Secretary. Its chief instigator was Bill Vincent, American
Ireland Fund Vice Chairman, she adds.
<P>
Four annual fundraisers for the German Ireland Fund have taken place since in
Munich and Koln with the most recent in Koln on November 18. In Berlin, a
relaxing "Jazzbrunch" was held October 29 to benefit the GIF
<P>
Future plans for the Fund are to build on the growing commercial, sporting and
cultural links that exist between Germany and Ireland. There are over 25,000
Irish people living in Germany, and Ireland is one of Germany's fastest growing
tourist destinations.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<P>
<HR SIZE=3 WIDTH=80%>

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p25b.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p25b-sml.gif"
BORDER=0 ALIGN=CENTER></A>

Konrad Adenauer, Chairman of the German Ireland Fund.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>

<P>
<A HREF="graphics/p25c.gif"><IMG WIDTH="78" HEIGHT="63" SRC="graphics/p25c-sml.gif"
BORDER=0 ALIGN=LEFT></A>
<BR>
Dr. Marie Therese Schmitz-Eichoff, Vlce-Chairman of the German Ireland Fund.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>

<P>
